1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,810
Everyone I talked to said, in effect, I'd love that.

2
00:00:04,321 --> 00:00:09,571
I continued to think about it and to figure how I could turn the idea into profit.

3
00:00:09,841 --> 00:00:14,210
Then one day, as I was driving to work, the answer came out of nowhere.

4
00:00:14,321 --> 00:00:17,891
Why not buy a farm and divide it into estates?

5
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:24,051
I figured the land might be worth more in relatively small pieces than in one big piece.

6
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:32,690
Twenty-two miles from the center of the city, I found a worn-out fifty-acre farm priced at $8,500.

7
00:00:32,881 --> 00:00:38,690
I bought it, paying only one-third down and working out a mortgage with the owner for the balance.

8
00:00:39,361 --> 00:00:43,250
Next, I planted pine seedlings where there were no trees.

9
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:47,650
I did this because a real estate man, whom I feel knows his business,

10
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:51,891
told me, people want trees these days, lots of trees.

11
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:59,971
I wanted my prospective buyers to see that in a few years, their estate would be covered with beautiful pine trees.

12
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:06,210
Then I got a surveyor to divide the 50 acres into 10 5-acre plots.

13
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,690
Now I was ready to start selling.

14
00:01:08,801 --> 00:01:15,891
I got several mailing lists of young executives in the city and put on a small-scale direct mail campaign.

15
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:22,931
I pointed out how for only $3,000, the price of a small city lot, they could buy an estate.

16
00:01:23,281 --> 00:01:27,891
I also described the potentials for recreation and wholesome living.

17
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:34,690
In six weeks' time, working only evenings and on weekends, I sold all ten plots.

18
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:37,571
Total income, $30,000.

19
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:45,571
Total costs, including the land, advertising, surveying and legal expenses, $10,400.

20
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:49,170
Profit, $19,600.

21
00:01:49,841 --> 00:01:56,531
I made a nice profit because I let myself be exposed to ideas of other intelligent people.

22
00:01:56,720 --> 00:02:04,051
Had I not accepted that invitation to attend a luncheon with a group completely foreign to my occupational interests,

23
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:08,851
my brain would have never worked out this successful plan for making a profit.

24
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:17,250
There are many ways to get mental stimulation, but here are two that you can incorporate into your pattern of life.

25
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:27,011
First, join and meet regularly with at least one professional group that provides stimulation in your own occupational area.

26
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:31,891
Rub shoulders and minds with other success-oriented people.

27
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:38,290
So often I hear someone say, I picked up a great idea this noon at the blank meeting,

28
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:41,971
or during the meeting yesterday I got to thinking.

29
00:02:42,321 --> 00:02:51,411
Remember, a mind that feeds only on itself soon is undernourished, becoming weak and incapable of creative progressive thought.

30
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:55,331
Stimulation from others is excellent mind food.

31
00:02:56,160 --> 00:03:02,770
Second, join and participate in at least one group outside your occupational interests.

32
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:10,290
Association with people who have different job interests broadens your thinking and helps you to see the big picture.

33
00:03:10,801 --> 00:03:19,331
You'll be surprised how mixing regularly with people outside your occupational area will stimulate your on-the-job thinking.

